      • getActiveKeyword

        java.lang.String getActiveKeyword()
        The keyword used by the main report which will enable or disable this report.
        Returns:
        the String name of the keyword which should be set true if this report is to be included in the main report.

      • setReportParameters

        boolean setReportParameters​(html.Template t,
                            AbstractModel model,
                            Report[] active_reports,
                            Content content)
        Defines all appropriate parameters in the template file for this report.
        Parameters:
        t - the Template used to display model properties.
        model - the AbstractModel that contains data which to display.
        active_reports - the Report[] list of reports currently being written.
        content - the Content which contains table of contents information for this report.
        Returns:
        a boolean value which determines if the report should be included in the main report. (This is useful when a report is requested, but no data exists for the report)
